<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102524295222601></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102524295222601><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=12793&mid=102524295222601>RE: Why do all the weapons suck?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=12793&mid=102524295222601#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=150564><span id= >Steric</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>19 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 28th 1:52 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Facts about melee 101.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;First offhand and main hand are independent of each other, so don't worry about matching delays.  Put a lightstone in your primary slot and watch your off-hand still swing if you don't believe me.<br>  <br>  Second the main difference between primary hand and secondary hand (other than the primary swings more) is the damage bonus.  One of the reasons low delay weapons are so sought after is that your damage bonus is the same for all one handed weapons.  The damage bonus is added to whatever damage you would normally do w/ the weapon everytime you hit the mob.  If your damage bonus is 10, everytime you hit the mob w/ your primary weapon you do 10 more damage than if you had swung the weapon as your secondary.  If you swing alot you get the damage bonus more.  This is the reason the wurmslayer is not nearly as good of a high end weapon as it is a low level (also the reason wurmies are primary only; they would be far too good in the offhand).  Therefore low delay is much more important in the primary hand.  If you are a warrior you probably want fairly low delay in both hands as more hits pisses the mobs off more.<br><br>Now that we know that our hands operate independently, and understand how damage bonus works, we can draw some conclusions about what we need in our secondary slot.  Going for damage only is stupid.  Doesn't matter if you hit for 100 damage if you only do it once a battle.  Going for pure low delay is not as effective as with the primary, because of the lack of damage bonus.  Therefore the main thing to look for in an off-hand weapon is ratio.  You want something that is going to do the best damage/second.<br><br>Some examples using common weapons.  If you had a lammy (9/19) and a centi LS (14/27) in almost all cases you would be better off w/ the centi in your secondary weapon slot, even though it costs about 1/2 to 2/3 of the pp on my server.  For primary (assuming you are of level to have a significant damage bonus) the lammy is a far superior weapon as its low delay allows for the damage bonus to be applied much more often.  The only reason for dueling lammies is to keep agro.<br>  <br>Okay I think I have been long winded enough now, I hope this helps (if anyone ever actually reads this heh).<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
